@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Iarrow" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

                             How to play?

  Clicking on an arrow will make it rotate 90 degres clockwise, unless
that arrow is immediately next to and points towards the empty space. In
that case, the arrow will move to the position occupied by the empty
space.

  To complicate matters a little, every time you move or rotate an arrow
and the empty space is not located at the lower right part of the game
board, an arrow will randomly rotate.

  A "Best moves" indicator at the right of the game board shows the
lowest number of moves that have been made for the current board size.

  Have fun!

OPTIONS:

  The following buttons appear at the right of the game board:

  New Game:  To restart a game.

  4x4...8x8: To choose between game board sizes from a 4 by 4 tile
             size to an 8 by 8 tile size board.

